        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): add defensive check for channel runtime initialization #87646",
        "body": "## What\n\nFixes #87646. Adds a guard to all Feishu inbound dispatch paths (DM, broadcast-active, broadcast-observer) so missing `core.channel.inbound.run` during cold starts does not crash the handler or silently drop messages.\n\n## How\n\n1. **`getChannelInboundRun()` helper** — validates that `core.channel.inbound.run` is a function. If missing, it **throws** (not returns null) so the error propagates to the webhook handler, allowing Feishu to retry delivery.\n\n2. **Rethrow in catch** — the outer `catch` in `handleFeishuMessage` specifically rethrows `channel runtime not ready` errors so they escape to the webhook handler and produce a non-2xx HTTP response.\n\n3. **All 3 dispatch paths guarded** — DM (line ~1689), broadcast-active (line ~1525), broadcast-observer (line ~1585).\n\n4. **Test updated** — expects `rejects.toThrow(/channel runtime not ready/)` instead of silent resolution.\n\n## Behavioral proof\n\nThe fix ensures that when `core.channel.inbound.run` is undefined:\n- The guard throws with a diagnostic log including channel/inbound key state\n- The throw escapes `handleFeishuMessage`'s catch block (selective rethrow)\n- The webhook handler returns non-2xx → Feishu retries the message\n- Messages are NOT permanently dropped or marked as processed\n\n> **Note:** Live Feishu gateway proof is not available in this contributor's environment (WeChat/Telegram only). The fix is validated through source analysis and mocked tests. A maintainer with a Feishu gateway can verify by checking that cold-start messages produce retryable 5xx responses instead of silent drops.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/feishu/src/bot.ts`: +34/-5 (helper + 3 guard call sites + rethrow)\n- `extensions/feishu/src/bot.test.ts`: +37/-1 (updated regression test)\n",
